Burkina president shuffles cabinet after election . Burkina Faso ' s President Blaise Compaore has shuffled his cabinet following his party ' s win in May 11 general elections , an official statement said . The new cabinet , proposed by Prime Minister Kadre Desire Ouedraogo , appoints Albert Millogo as defence minister to replace Colonel Badaye Fayama , and retires Hermann Yameogo as minister of state for solidarity and African integration . The cabinet announced on Tuesday evening has six new ministers , one new minister of state and two new deputy ministers . It is made up entirely of members or supporters of Compaore ' s ruling Congress for Democracy and Progress ( CDP ) , which won 97 of the new assembly ' s 111 seats in the election . The finance , foreign affairs and mines ministers remain the same . 
